Voters in Glasgow have their say on the Scottish independence referendum including one young Scot who bravely sings Dougie Maclean’s Caledonia Scottish independence video: Glasgow voters Voters in Glasgow have their say on the Scottish independence referendum including one young Scot who bravely sings Dougie Maclean’s Caledonia.

With Scotland’s polling stations witnessing a record turnout, we took to the streets of Scotland’s largest city to canvass opinion. 
Supporters of the Yes and No camps both gave their views on the vote with all agreeing, no matter what the outcome, the country will be changed forever. 

 